The '''Hesperange communal council''' ({{lang-fr|Conseil communal de Hesperange}}) is the [[Local government|local council]] for the [[Communes of Luxembourg|commune]] of [[Hesperange]], in southern [[Luxembourg]].
It consists of fifteen members, elected every six years by [[proportional representation]].<ref name="Conseil communal">{{cite web|url=http://www.hesperange.lu/Default.aspx?id=f5f2f902-06d0-489a-bc16-4fe2e3ee5e9b |title=Le Conseil Communal |accessdate=2007-09-16 |date= |publisher=Commune of Hesperange |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070722080746/http://www.hesperange.lu/Default.aspx?id=f5f2f902-06d0-489a-bc16-4fe2e3ee5e9b |archivedate=2007-07-22 |language=fr |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> The last elections were held on 9 October 2005, and resulted in a victory for the [[Christian Social People's Party]] (CSV). In the ''[[Collège échevinal (Luxembourg)|collège échevinal]]'', the CSV forms a coalition with [[Democratic Party (Luxembourg)|Democratic Party]] (DP), who have the second-largest contingent, under the leadership of CSV [[Mayor of Hesperange|mayor]] [[Marc Lies]].<ref name="Conseil communal" />
