{{italic title}} {{speciesbox | name = ''Tarentola protogigas'' | image = | image_caption = | status = LC | status_system = IUCN3.1 | status_ref = | genus = Tarentola | species = protogigas | authority = [[Ulrich Joger|Joger]] (1984) | synonyms = * ''Tarentola protogigas hartogi'' Joger, 1993 * ''Tarentola protogigas protogigas'' Joger, 1984 | synonyms_ref =<ref name="RDB"/> }} '''''Tarentola protogigas''''' (English name: '''First Giant wood gecko''' or '''Giant Fogo wood gecko''') is a [[species]] of [[gecko]]s in the [[Family (biology)|family]] [[Phyllodactylidae]]. The species is [[Endemism|endemic]] to the [[Cape Verde]] Islands, where it is found in the southwest portion of the Western Barlavento Islands, including [[Fogo, Cape Verde|Fogo]], [[Brava, Cape Verde|Brava]] and the lesser [[Ilhéus Secos]]<ref name="RDB">{{NRDB species|genus=Tarentola |species=protogigas|accessdate=29 March 2017}}</ref> The species was named by [[Hans Hermann Schleich]] in 1984.
==Etymology== The [[specific name (zoology)|specific name]] is named after the Greek name for the "first giant" (''πρώτο'' ''proto'' and ''γίγας'' ''gigas'' (Modern Greek: ''γίγαντας'' ''gigantas'')).<ref name="RDB"/>
==Taxonomy== The subspecies were elevated from ''Tarentola rudis protogigas'' by Vasconcelos, Perera, Geniez, Harris & Carranza in 2012.<ref>Vasconcelos, Perera, Geniez, Harris & Carranza, ''An integrative taxonomic revision of the Tarentola geckos (Squamata, Phyllodactylidae) of the Cape Verde Islands.'' Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 2012, vol. 164, no. 2, p. 328-360</ref> Also that time, ''Tarentola rudis hartogi'' was placed under this species as a subspecies of ''Tarentola protogigas hartogi''
==Synonyms== *''Tarentola protogigas hartogi'' (Hartog's gecko) Joger, 1993 *''Tarentola protogigas protogigas'' Joger, 1984
