[[File:Traditional_dance_(tsutsube).jpg|thumb|200px|Tsutsube traditional dance]]
'''Tsutsube'''{{Pronunciation-needed}}  is a traditional dance in [[Botswana]] which is practiced by [[Basarwa]] or [[San people]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Wither the beloved Tsutsube |url=http://www.dailynews.gov.bw/news-details.php?nid=2957|accessdate=21 September 2017}}</ref>Tsutsube is performed in four ritualistic categories or stages which are the first kill, [[puberty]], marriage and [[trance]]. According to the history, the first kill was for males or boys, and trance dance was for healing purposes to engage [[ancestors]] spirits.

